This paper deals with the testability of digital ICs, specifically PUFs, which are used for hardware security. This topic falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the modeling of PUFs as Boolean functions, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and circuit complexity (cs.CC). The paper proposes a testing framework for PUFs, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper uses statistical tools to analyze the correlation-spectra of PUFs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
